keyFacts: An inter-office FBI call regarding the Epstein case was scheduled for October 11, 2019.
The call involved coordination between the FBI's New York (NY) and Washington, D.C. (DO) offices.
The subject of the call was a 'Miami Brief', suggesting ongoing investigative activity related to Epstein's activities in Florida.
The calendar entry indicates the meeting was classified as 'X-PERSONAL' and given high priority (5).
An 'Other Government Agency' (OGA) representative from New York was also listed as an attendee.
